  "text": "has the same eigenvalues (though now two copies of each), hence two eigenvalues larger than 1. By the stable manifold theorem, the local stable manifold near the origin has real codimension at least 2, and there exists a neighborhood V ⊂ U of the origin such that if X ∈ V is not in the local stable manifold, then H P f m (X) / ∈ V for some m ≥ 1 (refer to Theorems 10.6 and 10.7 of [CITATION_1] ). In particular, this implies the following.",
